This is a None task manager
===========================
notm is based on 'sentaku' (https://github.com/rcmdnk/sentaku)
tool which provides the menu-like navigation engine. The 'sentaku'
script is added as part of this repository and is installed
into ${PREFIX}/lib/notm, such approach does not require additional
installation of sentaku.

Navigation
==========
Use VIM style (h,j,k,l) navigation to browse
over tasks and states.

Create task
===========
1) Go to 'TASKS/'
2) Press 't' and, enter task name and press 'Enter'
3) Press 'l' to open created task and edit it.

Created task will be moved to TODO state.

Change task's state
===================
1) Select task from TASKS/ folder.
2) Change task state by:

    Ctr-P - move to IN-PROGRESS state
    Ctr-D - move to DONE state
    Ctr-T - move to TODO state
